article.description: — Jordan King's 21 points helped Richmond defeat UNLV 82-65 on Tuesday night in the Sunshine Slam.
article.headline: King's 21 lead Richmond past UNLV 82-65
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- — Jordan King's 21 points helped Richmond defeat UNLV 82-65 on Tuesday night in the Sunshine Slam. King also had six assists for the Spiders (3-2). Neal Quinn scored 20 points while going 9 of 16 from the field, and added seven rebounds, five assists, and four blocks. Isaiah Bigelow was 7-of-8 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 16 points. The Rebels (2-3) were led by Jackie Johnson III, who recorded 17 points. Kalib Boone added 14 points for UNLV. In addition, Jalen Hill had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
